    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Night Our Cable Went Dark</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jennifer Rosa letter on May 2 article holds Time Warner's withholding of ABC's programs justifies her decision not to pay for cable television</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Blackout of ABC on Cable Affects Millions of Homes'' (front page, May 2): I feel as if I have done something wrong when I have to say in conversation that I did not see that great episode of ''The Sopranos'' because I don't have cable.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Blackout of ABC on Cable Affects Millions of Homes'' (front page, May 2): I feel as if I have done something wrong when I have to say in conversation that I did not see that great episode of ''The Sopranos'' because I don't have cable.</p>
        <p>But on Monday night, while watching ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire,'' I finally felt vindicated by my decision to pinch pennies and stick to my antenna. For one night I was in the loop, even if everyone else wasn't.</p>
        <p>JENNIFER ROSA  Fresh Meadows, Queens, May 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
